obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (50026)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent, commencement and application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50026&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Consumer`
  line `Protection Act, 2019.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India except the State of Jammu and Kashmir.^*`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification, appoint and`
  line `different dates may be appointed for different States and for different provisions of this Act and any`
  line `reference in any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to the`
  line `coming into force of that provision.`
  line
  line `(4) Save as otherwise expressly provided by the Central Government, by notification, this Act shall`
  line `apply to all goods and services.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
  line
  line `1. 20th July, 2020.--- S. 2 [ Except clauses (4), (13), (14), (16), (40)], s. 3 to 9 (both inclusive), s. 28 to 73 (both inclusive) [Except`
  line `sub-clause (iv) of clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 58], s. 74 to 81 (both inclusive), s. 82 to 87 (both inclusive), s. 90 and`
  line `91 [Except sections 88, 89, 92 and 93], s. 95, 98,100 and 101 Except clauses (f) to (m) and clauses (zg), (zh) and (zi) of subsection 2, s. 102, 103, 105, 106, 107 [ Except sections 94, 96, 97, 99, 104], vide notification No. S.O. 2351(E), dated`
  line `15th July, 2020, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `24th July, 2020.--- S.[ 2 clauses (4), (13), (14), (16), (40)], s. 10 to 27 (both inclusive), sub-clause (iv) of clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 58, s. 88, 89, 92 and 93, 94, 96, 97 and 99, clause (f) to (m) of sub-section 2 and clauses (zg), (zh)`
  line `and (zi) of sub-section 2 of s. 101, 104, vide notification No. S.O. 2421(E), dated 23rd July 2020, see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (50027)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50027&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,---`
  line
  line `(1) "advertisement" means any audio or visual publicity, representation, endorsement or`
  line `pronouncement made by means of light, sound, smoke, gas, print, electronic media, internet or`
  line `website and includes any notice, circular, label, wrapper, invoice or such other documents;`
  line
  line `(2) "appropriate laboratory" means a laboratory or an organisation---`
  line
  line `(i) recognised by the Central Government; or`
  line
  line `(ii) recognised by a State Government, subject to such guidelines as may be issued by the`
  line `Central Government in this behalf; or`
  line
  line `(iii) established by or under any law for the time being in force, which is maintained,`
  line `financed or aided by the Central Government or a State Government for carrying out analysis or`
  line `test of any goods with a view to determining whether such goods suffer from any defect;`
  line
  line `(3) "branch office" means ---`
  line
  line `(i) any office or place of work described as a branch by the establishment; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any establishment carrying on either the same or substantially the same activity carried on`
  line `by the head office of the establishment;`
  line
  line `(4) "Central Authority" means the Central Consumer Protection Authority established under`
  line `section 10;`
  line
  line `(5) "complainant" means ---`
  line
  line `(i) a consumer; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any voluntary consumer association registered under any law for the time being in force; or`
  line
  line `(iii) the Central Government or any State Government; or`
  line
  line `(iv) the Central Authority; or`
  line
  line `(v) one or more consumers, where there are numerous consumers having the same interest; or`
  line
  line `(vi) in case of death of a consumer, his legal heir or legal representative; or`
  line
  line `(vii) in case of a consumer being a minor, his parent or legal guardian;`
  line
  line `(6) "complaint" means any allegation in writing, made by a complainant for obtaining any relief`
  line `provided by or under this Act, that ---`
  line
  line `(i) an unfair contract or unfair trade practice or a restrictive trade practice has been adopted`
  line `by any trader or service provider;`
  line
  line `(ii) the goods bought by him or agreed to be bought by him suffer from one or more defects;`
  line
  line `(iii) the services hired or availed of or agreed to be hired or availed of by him suffer from any`
  line deficiency;
  line
  line `(iv) a trader or a service provider, as the case may be, has charged for the goods or for the`
  line `services mentioned in the complaint, a price in excess of the price ---`
  line
  line `(a) fixed by or under any law for the time being in force; or`
  line
  line `(b) displayed on the goods or any package containing such goods; or`
  line
  line `(c) displayed on the price list exhibited by him by or under any law for the time being in`
  line `force; or`
  line
  line `(d) agreed between the parties;`
  line
  line `(v) the goods, which are hazardous to life and safety when used, are being offered for sale to`
  line `the public--`
  line
  line `(a) in contravention of standards relating to safety of such goods as required to be`
  line `complied with, by or under any law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(b) where the trader knows that the goods so offered are unsafe to the public;`
  line
  line `(vi) the services which are hazardous or likely to be hazardous to life and safety of the public`
  line `when used, are being offered by a person who provides any service and who knows it to be`
  line `injurious to life and safety;`
  line
  line `(vii) a claim for product liability action lies against the product manufacturer, product seller`
  line `or product service provider, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(7) "consumer" means any person who ---`
  line
  line `(i) buys any goods for a consideration which has been paid or promised or partly paid and`
  line `partly promised, or under any system of deferred payment and includes any user of such`
  line `goods other than the person who buys such goods for consideration paid or promised or partly`
  line `paid or partly promised, or under any system of deferred payment, when such use is made`
  line `with the approval of such person, but does not include a person who obtains such goods for`
  line `resale or for any commercial purpose; or`
  line
  line `(ii) hires or avails of any service for a consideration which has been paid or promised or`
  line `partly paid and partly promised, or under any system of deferred payment and includes any`
  line `beneficiary of such service other than the person who hires or avails of the services for`
  line `consideration paid or promised, or partly paid and partly promised, or under any system of`
  line `deferred payment, when such services are availed of with the approval of the first mentioned`
  line `person, but does not include a person who avails of such service for any commercial purpose.`
  line
  line `Explanation. --For the purposes of this clause, --`
  line
  line `(a) the expression "commercial purpose" does not include use by a person of goods`
  line `bought and used by him exclusively for the purpose of earning his livelihood, by means`
  line `of self-employment;`
  line
  line `(b) the expressions "buys any goods" and "hires or avails any services" includes`
  line `offline or online transactions through electronic means or by teleshopping or direct`
  line `selling or multi-level marketing;`
  line
  line `(8) "consumer dispute" means a dispute where the person against whom a complaint has been`
  line `made, denies or disputes the allegations contained in the complaint;`
  line
  line `(9) "consumer rights" includes,--`
  line
  line `(i) the right to be protected against the marketing of goods, products or services which are`
  line `hazardous to life and property;`
  line
  line `(ii) the right to be informed about the quality, quantity, potency, purity, standard and price of`
  line `goods, products or services, as the case may be, so as to protect the consumer against unfair trade`
  line practices;
  line
  line `(iii) the right to be assured, wherever possible, access to a variety of goods, products or`
  line `services at competitive prices;`
  line
  line `(iv) the right to be heard and to be assured that consumer's interests will receive due`
  line `consideration at appropriate fora;`
  line
  line `(v) the right to seek redressal against unfair trade practice or restrictive trade practices or`
  line `unscrupulous exploitation of consumers; and`
  line
  line `(vi) the right to consumer awareness;`
  line
  line `(10) "defect" means any fault, imperfection or shortcoming in the quality, quantity, potency,`
  line `purity or standard which is required to be maintained by or under any law for the time being in force`
  line `or under any contract, express or implied or as is claimed by the trader in any manner whatsoever in`
  line `relation to any goods or product and the expression "defective" shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(11) "deficiency" means any fault, imperfection, shortcoming or inadequacy in the quality, nature`
  line `and manner of performance which is required to be maintained by or under any law for the time being`
  line `in force or has been undertaken to be performed by a person in pursuance of a contract or otherwise in`
  line `relation to any service and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) any act of negligence or omission or commission by such person which causes loss or`
  line `injury to the consumer; and`
  line
  line `(ii) deliberate withholding of relevant information by such person to the consumer;`
  line
  line `(12) "design", in relation to a product, means the intended or known physical and material`
  line `characteristics of such product and includes any intended or known formulation or content of such`
  line `product and the usual result of the intended manufacturing or other process used to produce such`
  line product;
  line
  line `(13) "direct selling" means marketing, distribution and sale of goods or provision of services`
  line `through a network of sellers, other than through a permanent retail location;`
  line
  line `(14) "Director-General" means the Director-General appointed under sub-section (2) of section`
  line 15;
  line
  line `(15) "District Commission" means a District Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission`
  line `established under sub-section (1) of section 28;`
  line
  line `(16) "e-commerce" means buying or selling of goods or services including digital products over`
  line `digital or electronic network;`
  line
  line `(17) "electronic service provider" means a person who provides technologies or processes to`
  line `enable a product seller to engage in advertising or selling goods or services to a consumer and`
  line `includes any online market place or online auction sites;`
  line
  line `(18) "endorsement", in relation to an advertisement, means--`
  line
  line `(i) any message, verbal statement, demonstration; or`
  line
  line `(ii) depiction of the name, signature, likeness or other identifiable personal characteristics of`
  line `an individual; or`
  line
  line `(iii) depiction of the name or seal of any institution or organisation, which makes the`
  line `consumer to believe that it reflects the opinion, finding or experience of the person making such`
  line endorsement;
  line
  line `(19) "establishment" includes an advertising agency, commission agent, manufacturing, trading`
  line `or any other commercial agency which carries on any business, trade or profession or any work in`
  line `connection with or incidental or ancillary to any commercial activity, trade or profession, or such`
  line `other class or classes of persons including public utility entities in the manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(20) "express warranty" means any material statement, affirmation of fact, promise or description`
  line `relating to a product or service warranting that it conforms to such material statement, affirmation,`
  line `promise or description and includes any sample or model of a product warranting that the whole of`
  line `such product conforms to such sample or model;`
  line
  line `(21) "goods" means every kind of movable property and includes "food" as defined in clause (j)`
  line `of sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Food Safety and Standards Act, 2006 (34 of 2006);`
  line
  line `(22) "harm", in relation to a product liability, includes---`
  line
  line `(i) damage to any property, other than the product itself;`
  line
  line `(ii) personal injury, illness or death;`
  line
  line `(iii) mental agony or emotional distress attendant to personal injury or illness or damage to`
  line `property; or`
  line
  line `(iv) any loss of consortium or services or other loss resulting from a harm referred to in subclause (i) or sub-clause (ii) or sub-clause (iii), but shall not include any harm caused to a product`
  line `itself or any damage to the property on account of breach of warranty conditions or any`
  line `commercial or economic loss, including any direct, incidental or consequential loss relating`
  line thereto;
  line
  line `(23) "injury" means any harm whatever illegally caused to any person, in body, mind or property;`
  line
  line `(24) "manufacturer" means a person who---`
  line
  line `(i) makes any goods or parts thereof; or`
  line
  line `(ii) assembles any goods or parts thereof made by others; or`
  line
  line `(iii) puts or causes to be put his own mark on any goods made by any other person;`
  line
  line `(25) "mediation" means the process by which a mediator mediates the consumer disputes;`
  line
  line `(26) "mediator" means a mediator referred to in section 75;`
  line
  line `(27) "member" includes the President and a member of the National Commission or a State`
  line `Commission or a District Commission, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(28) "misleading advertisement" in relation to any product or service, means an advertisement,`
  line which---
  line
  line `(i) falsely describes such product or service; or`
  line
  line `(ii) gives a false guarantee to, or is likely to mislead the consumers as to the nature,`
  line `substance, quantity or quality of such product or service; or`
  line
  line `(iii) conveys an express or implied representation which, if made by the manufacturer or`
  line `seller or service provider thereof, would constitute an unfair trade practice; or`
  line
  line `(iv) deliberately conceals important information;`
  line
  line `(29) "National Commission" means the National Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission`
  line `established under sub-section (1) of section 53;`
  line
  line `(30) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette and the term "notify"`
  line `shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(31) "person" includes---`
  line
  line `(i) an individual;`
  line
  line `(ii) a firm whether registered or not;`
  line
  line `(iii) a Hindu undivided family;`
  line
  line `(iv) a co-operative society;`
  line
  line `(v) an association of persons whether registered under the Societies Registration Act, 1860`
  line `(21 of 1860) or not;`
  line
  line `(vi) any corporation, company or a body of individuals whether incorporated or not;`
  line
  line `(vii) any artificial juridical person, not falling within any of the preceding sub-clauses;`
  line
  line `(32) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made by the Central Government, or, as the case may`
  line `be, the State Government;`
  line
  line `(33) "product" means any article or goods or substance or raw material or any extended cycle of`
  line `such product, which may be in gaseous, liquid, or solid state possessing intrinsic value which is`
  line `capable of delivery either as wholly assembled or as a component part and is produced for`
  line `introduction to trade or commerce, but does not include human tissues, blood, blood products and`
  line organs;
  line
  line `(34) "product liability" means the responsibility of a product manufacturer or product seller, of`
  line `any product or service, to compensate for any harm caused to a consumer by such defective product`
  line `manufactured or sold or by deficiency in services relating thereto;`
  line
  line `(35) "product liability action" means a complaint filed by a person before a District Commission`
  line `or State Commission or National Commission, as the case may be, for claiming compensation for the`
  line `harm caused to him;`
  line
  line `(36) "product manufacturer" means a person who---`
  line
  line `(i) makes any product or parts thereof; or`
  line
  line `(ii) assembles parts thereof made by others; or`
  line
  line `(iii) puts or causes to be put his own mark on any products made by any other person; or`
  line
  line `(iv) makes a product and sells, distributes, leases, installs, prepares, packages, labels, markets,`
  line `repairs, maintains such product or is otherwise involved in placing such product for commercial`
  line `purpose; or`
  line
  line `(v) designs, produces, fabricates, constructs or re-manufactures any product before its sale; or`
  line
  line `(vi) being a product seller of a product, is also a manufacturer of such product;`
  line
  line `(37) "product seller", in relation to a product, means a person who, in the course of business,`
  line `imports, sells, distributes, leases, installs, prepares, packages, labels, markets, repairs, maintains, or`
  line `otherwise is involved in placing such product for commercial purpose and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) a manufacturer who is also a product seller; or`
  line
  line `(ii) a service provider,`
  line
  line `but does not include---`
  line
  line `(a) a seller of immovable property, unless such person is engaged in the sale of`
  line `constructed house or in the construction of homes or flats;`
  line
  line `(b) a provider of professional services in any transaction in which, the sale or use of a`
  line `product is only incidental thereto, but furnishing of opinion, skill or services being the`
  line `essence of such transaction;`
  line
  line `(c) a person who--`
  line
  line `(I) acts only in a financial capacity with respect to the sale of the product;`
  line
  line `(II) is not a manufacturer, wholesaler, distributor, retailer, direct seller or an`
  line `electronic service provider;`
  line
  line `(III) leases a product, without having a reasonable opportunity to inspect and`
  line `discover defects in the product, under a lease arrangement in which the selection,`
  line `possession, maintenance, and operation of the product are controlled by a person other`
  line `than the lessor;`
  line
  line `(38) "product service provider", in relation to a product, means a person who provides any service`
  line `in respect of such product;`
  line
  line `(39) "regulations" means the regulations made by the National Commission, or as the case may`
  line `be, the Central Authority;`
  line
  line `(40) "Regulator" means a body or any authority established under any other law for the time`
  line `being in force;`
  line
  line `(41) "restrictive trade practice" means a trade practice which tends to bring about manipulation of`
  line `price or its conditions of delivery or to affect flow of supplies in the market relating to goods or`
  line `services in such a manner as to impose on the consumers unjustified costs or restrictions and shall`
  line include--
  line
  line `(i) delay beyond the period agreed to by a trader in supply of such goods or in providing`
  line `the services which has led or is likely to lead to rise in the price;`
  line
  line `(ii) any trade practice which requires a consumer to buy, hire or avail of any goods or, as`
  line `the case may be, services as condition precedent for buying, hiring or availing of other goods`
  line `or services;`
  line
  line `(42) "service" means service of any description which is made available to potential users and`
  line `includes, but not limited to, the provision of facilities in connection with banking, financing,`
  line `insurance, transport, processing, supply of electrical or other energy, telecom, boarding or`
  line `lodging or both, housing construction, entertainment, amusement or the purveying of news or`
  line `other information, but does not include the rendering of any service free of charge or under a`
  line `contract of personal service;`
  line
  line `(43) "spurious goods" means such goods which are falsely claimed to be genuine;`
  line
  line `(44) "State Commission" means a State Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission`
  line `established under sub-section (1) of section 42;`
  line
  line `(45) "trader", in relation to any goods, means a person who sells or distributes any goods for`
  line `sale and includes the manufacturer thereof, and where such goods are sold or distributed in`
  line `package form, includes the packer thereof;`
  line
  line `(46) "unfair contract" means a contract between a manufacturer or trader or service provider`
  line `on one hand, and a consumer on the other, having such terms which cause significant change in`
  line `the rights of such consumer, including the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) requiring manifestly excessive security deposits to be given by a consumer for the`
  line `performance of contractual obligations; or`
  line
  line `(ii) imposing any penalty on the consumer, for the breach of contract thereof which is`
  line `wholly disproportionate to the loss occurred due to such breach to the other party to the`
  line `contract; or`
  line
  line `(iii) refusing to accept early repayment of debts on payment of applicable penalty; or`
  line
  line `(iv) entitling a party to the contract to terminate such contract unilaterally, without`
  line `reasonable cause; or`
  line
  line `(v) permitting or has the effect of permitting one party to assign the contract to the`
  line `detriment of the other party who is a consumer, without his consent; or`
  line
  line `(vi) imposing on the consumer any unreasonable charge, obligation or condition which`
  line `puts such consumer to disadvantage;`
  line
  line `(47) "unfair trade practice" means a trade practice which, for the purpose of promoting the sale,`
  line `use or supply of any goods or for the provision of any service, adopts any unfair method or unfair or`
  line `deceptive practice including any of the following practices, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) making any statement, whether orally or in writing or by visible representation including`
  line `by means of electronic record, which--`
  line
  line `(a) falsely represents that the goods are of a particular standard, quality, quantity, grade,`
  line `composition, style or model;`
  line
  line `(b) falsely represents that the services are of a particular standard, quality or grade;`
  line
  line `(c) falsely represents any re-built, second-hand, renovated, reconditioned or old goods as`
  line `new goods;`
  line
  line `(d) represents that the goods or services have sponsorship, approval, performance,`
  line `characteristics, accessories, uses or benefits which such goods or services do not have;`
  line
  line `(e) represents that the seller or the supplier has a sponsorship or approval or affiliation`
  line `which such seller or supplier does not have;`
  line
  line `(f) makes a false or misleading representation concerning the need for, or the usefulness`
  line `of, any goods or services;`
  line
  line `(g) gives to the public any warranty or guarantee of the performance, efficacy or length of`
  line `life of a product or of any goods that is not based on an adequate or proper test thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a defence is raised to the effect that such warranty or guarantee is`
  line `based on adequate or proper test, the burden of proof of such defence shall lie on the person`
  line `raising such defence;`
  line
  line `(h) makes to the public a representation in a form that purports to be--`
  line
  line `(A) a warranty or guarantee of a product or of any goods or services; or`
  line
  line `(B) a promise to replace, maintain or repair an article or any part thereof or to repeat`
  line `or continue a service until it has achieved a specified result, if such purported warranty or`
  line `guarantee or promise is materially misleading or if there is no reasonable prospect that`
  line `such warranty, guarantee or promise will be carried out;`
  line
  line `(i) materially misleads the public concerning the price at which a product or like products or`
  line `goods or services, have been or are, ordinarily sold or provided, and, for this purpose, a`
  line `representation as to price shall be deemed to refer to the price at which the product or goods or`
  line `services has or have been sold by sellers or provided by suppliers generally in the relevant market`
  line `unless it is clearly specified to be the price at which the product has been sold or services have`
  line `been provided by the person by whom or on whose behalf the representation is made;`
  line
  line `(j) gives false or misleading facts disparaging the goods, services or trade of another person.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-clause, a statement that is,--`
  line
  line `(A) expressed on an article offered or displayed for sale, or on its wrapper or container; or`
  line
  line `(B) expressed on anything attached to, inserted in, or accompanying, an article offered or`
  line `displayed for sale, or on anything on which the article is mounted for display or sale; or`
  line
  line `(C) contained in or on anything that is sold, sent, delivered, transmitted or in any other`
  line `manner whatsoever made available to a member of the public,`
  line
  line `shall be deemed to be a statement made to the public by, and only by, the person who had`
  line `caused the statement to be so expressed, made or contained;`
  line
  line `(ii) permitting the publication of any advertisement, whether in any newspaper or otherwise,`
  line `including by way of electronic record, for the sale or supply at a bargain price of goods or`
  line `services that are not intended to be offered for sale or supply at the bargain price, or for a period`
  line `that is, and in quantities that are, reasonable, having regard to the nature of the market in which`
  line `the business is carried on, the nature and size of business, and the nature of the advertisement.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this sub-clause, "bargain price" means,--`
  line
  line `(A) a price that is stated in any advertisement to be a bargain price, by reference to an`
  line `ordinary price or otherwise; or`
  line
  line `(B) a price that a person who reads, hears or sees the advertisement, would reasonably`
  line `understand to be a bargain price having regard to the prices at which the product advertised or`
  line `like products are ordinarily sold;`
  line
  line `(iii) permitting--`
  line
  line `(a) the offering of gifts, prizes or other items with the intention of not providing them as`
  line `offered or creating impression that something is being given or offered free of charge when it`
  line `is fully or partly covered by the amount charged, in the transaction as a whole;`
  line
  line `(b) the conduct of any contest, lottery, game of chance or skill, for the purpose of`
  line `promoting, directly or indirectly, the sale, use or supply of any product or any business`
  line `interest, except such contest, lottery, game of chance or skill as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(c) withholding from the participants of any scheme offering gifts, prizes or other items`
  line `free of charge on its closure, the information about final results of the scheme.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this sub-clause, the participants of a scheme shall be`
  line `deemed to have been informed of the final results of the scheme where such results are within`
  line `a reasonable time published, prominently in the same newspaper in which the scheme was`
  line `originally advertised;`
  line
  line `(iv) permitting the sale or supply of goods intended to be used, or are of a kind likely to`
  line `be used by consumers, knowing or having reason to believe that the goods do not comply`
  line `with the standards prescribed by the competent authority relating to performance,`
  line `composition, contents, design, constructions, finishing or packaging as are necessary to`
  line `prevent or reduce the risk of injury to the person using the goods;`
  line
  line `(v) permitting the hoarding or destruction of goods, or refusal to sell the goods or to make`
  line `them available for sale or to provide any service, if such hoarding or destruction or refusal`
  line `raises or tends to raise or is intended to raise, the cost of those or other similar goods or`
  line services;
  line
  line `(vi) manufacturing of spurious goods or offering such goods for sale or adopting`
  line `deceptive practices in the provision of services;`
  line
  line `(vii) not issuing bill or cash memo or receipt for the goods sold or services rendered in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(viii) refusing, after selling goods or rendering services, to take back or withdraw`
  line `defective goods or to withdraw or discontinue deficient services and to refund the`
  line `consideration thereof, if paid, within the period stipulated in the bill or cash memo or receipt`
  line `or in the absence of such stipulation, within a period of thirty days;`
  line
  line `(ix) disclosing to other person any personal information given in confidence by the`
  line `consumer unless such disclosure is made in accordance with the provisions of any law for the`
  line `time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (50028)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Central Consumer Protection Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50028&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by notification,`
  line `establish with effect from such date as it may specify in that notification, the Central Consumer Protection`
  line `Council to be known as the Central Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Council shall be an advisory council and consist of the following members,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Minister-in-charge of the Department of Consumer Affairs in the Central Government,`
  line `who shall be the Chairperson; and`
  line
  line `(b) such number of other official or non-official members representing such interests as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (50029)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Procedure for meetings of Central Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50029&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Council shall meet as and when`
  line `necessary, but at least one meeting of the Council shall be held every year.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Council shall meet at such time and place as the Chairperson may think fit and shall`
  line `observe such procedure in regard to the transaction of its business as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (50030)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Objects of Central Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50030&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The objects of the Central Council shall be to render advice on`
  line `promotion and protection of the consumers' rights under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (50031)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `State Consumer Protection Councils.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50031&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every State Government shall, by notification,`
  line `establish with effect from such date as it may specify in such notification, a State Consumer Protection`
  line `Council for such State to be known as the State Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Council shall be an advisory council and consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Minister-in-charge of Consumer Affairs in the State Government who shall be the`
  line Chairperson;
  line
  line `(b) such number of other official or non-official members representing such interests as may be`
  line prescribed;
  line
  line `(c) such number of other official or non-official members, not exceeding ten, as may be`
  line `nominated by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Council shall meet as and when necessary but not less than two meetings shall be held`
  line `every year.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Council shall meet at such time and place as the Chairperson may think fit and shall`
  line `observe such procedure in regard to the transaction of its business, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (50032)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Objects of State Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50032&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The objects of every State Council shall be to render advice on`
  line `promotion and protection of consumer rights under this Act within the State.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (50033)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `District Consumer Protection Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50033&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall, by notification,`
  line `establish for every District with effect from such date as it may specify in such notification, a District`
  line `Consumer Protection Council to be known as the District Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The District Council shall be an advisory council and consist of the following members,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Collector of the district (by whatever name called), who shall be the Chairperson; and`
  line
  line `(b) such number of other official and non-official members representing such interests as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) The District Council shall meet as and when necessary but not less than two meetings shall be`
  line `held every year.`
  line
  line `(4) The District Council shall meet at such time and place within the district as the Chairperson may`
  line `think fit and shall observe such procedure in regard to the transaction of its business as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (50034)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Objects of District Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50034&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The objects of every District Council shall be to render advice on`
  line `promotion and protection of consumer rights under this Act within the district.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (50035)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Establishment of Central Consumer Protection Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50035&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government`
  line `shall, by notification, establish with effect from such date as it may specify in that notification, a Central`
  line `Consumer Protection Authority to be known as the Central Authority to regulate matters relating to`
  line `violation of rights of consumers, unfair trade practices and false or misleading advertisements which are`
  line `prejudicial to the interests of public and consumers and to promote, protect and enforce the rights of`
  line `consumers as a class.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Authority shall consist of a Chief Commissioner and such number of other`
  line `Commissioners as may be prescribed, to be appointed by the Central Government to exercise the powers`
  line `and discharge the functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The headquarters of the Central Authority shall be at such place in the National Capital Region of`
  line `Delhi, and it shall have regional and other offices in any other place in India as the Central Government`
  line `may decide.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (50036)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Qualifications, method of recruitment, etc., of Chief Commissioner and Commissioners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50036&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification, make rules to provide for the qualifications for`
  line `appointment, method of recruitment, procedure for appointment, term of office, salaries and allowances,`
  line `resignation, removal and other terms and conditions of the service of the Chief Commissioner and`
  line `Commissioners of the Central Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (50037)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Vacancy, etc., not to invalidate proceedings of Central Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50037&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of`
  line `the Central Authority shall be invalid merely by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Central Authority; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as the Chief Commissioner or as a`
  line `Commissioner; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Central Authority not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (50038)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Appointment of officers, experts, professionals and other employees of Central Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50038&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall provide the Central Authority such number of officers and other`
  line `employees as it considers necessary for the efficient performance of its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `officers and other employees of the Central Authority appointed under this Act shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) The Central Authority may engage, in accordance with the procedure specified by regulations,`
  line `such number of experts and professionals of integrity and ability, who have special knowledge and`
  line `experience in the areas of consumer rights and welfare, consumer policy, law, medicine, food safety,`
  line `health, engineering, product safety, commerce, economics, public affairs or administration, as it deems`
  line `necessary to assist it in the discharge of its functions under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (50039)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Procedure of Central Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50039&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Authority shall regulate the procedure for`
  line `transaction of its business and allocation of its business amongst the Chief Commissioner and`
  line `Commissioners as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Commissioner shall have the powers of general superintendence, direction and control`
  line `in respect of all administrative matters of the Central Authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chief Commissioner may delegate such of his powers relating to administrative`
  line `matters of the Central Authority, as he may think fit, to any Commissioner (including Commissioner of a`
  line `regional office) or any other officer of the Central Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (50040)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Investigation Wing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50040&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Authority shall have an Investigation Wing headed by a`
  line `Director-General for the purpose of conducting inquiry or investigation under this Act as may be directed`
  line `by the Central Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may appoint a Director-General and such number of Additional`
  line `Director-General, Director, Joint Director, Deputy Director and Assistant Director, from amongst persons`
  line `who have experience in investigation and possess such qualifications, in such manner, as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) Every Additional Director-General, Director, Joint Director, Deputy Director and Assistant`
  line `Director shall exercise his powers, and discharge his functions, subject to the general control, supervision`
  line `and direction of the Director-General.`
  line
  line `(4) The Director-General may delegate all or any of his powers to the Additional Director-General or`
  line `Director, Joint Director or Deputy Director or Assistant Director, as the case may be, while conducting`
  line `inquiries or investigations under this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) The inquiries or the investigations made by the Director-General shall be submitted to the Central`
  line `Authority in such form, in such manner and within such time, as may be specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (50041)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Power of District Collector.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50041&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The District Collector (by whatever name called) may, on a`
  line `complaint or on a reference made to him by the Central Authority or the Commissioner of a regional`
  line `office, inquire into or investigate complaints regarding violation of rights of consumers as a class, on`
  line `matters relating to violations of consumer rights, unfair trade practices and false or misleading`
  line `advertisements, within his jurisdiction and submit his report to the Central Authority or to the`
  line `Commissioner of a regional office, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (50042)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Complaints to authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50042&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `A complaint relating to violation of consumer rights or unfair trade`
  line `practices or false or misleading advertisements which are prejudicial to the interests of consumers as a`
  line `class, may be forwarded either in writing or in electronic mode, to any one of the authorities, namely, the`
  line `District Collector or the Commissioner of regional office or the Central Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (50043)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Powers and functions of Central Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50043&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Authority shall--`
  line
  line `(a) protect, promote and enforce the rights of consumers as a class, and prevent violation of`
  line `consumers rights under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) prevent unfair trade practices and ensure that no person engages himself in unfair trade`
  line practices;
  line
  line `(c) ensure that no false or misleading advertisement is made of any goods or services which`
  line `contravenes the provisions of this Act or the rules or regulations made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(d) ensure that no person takes part in the publication of any advertisement which is false or`
  line misleading.
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions contained in sub-section (1), the Central`
  line `Authority may, for any of the purposes aforesaid,--`
  line
  line `(a) inquire or cause an inquiry or investigation to be made into violations of consumer rights or`
  line `unfair trade practices, either suo motu or on a complaint received or on the directions from the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(b) file complaints before the District Commission, the State Commission or the National`
  line `Commission, as the case may be, under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) intervene in any proceedings before the District Commission or the State Commission or the`
  line `National Commission, as the case may be, in respect of any allegation of violation of consumer rights`
  line `or unfair trade practices;`
  line
  line `(d) review the matters relating to, and the factors inhibiting enjoyment of, consumer rights,`
  line `including safeguards provided for the protection of consumers under any other law for the time being`
  line `in force and recommend appropriate remedial measures for their effective implementation;`
  line
  line `(e) recommend adoption of international covenants and best international practices on consumer`
  line `rights to ensure effective enforcement of consumer rights;`
  line
  line `(f) undertake and promote research in the field of consumer rights;`
  line
  line `(g) spread and promote awareness on consumer rights;`
  line
  line `(h) encourage non-Governmental organisations and other institutions working in the field of`
  line `consumer rights to co-operate and work with consumer protection agencies;`
  line
  line `(i) mandate the use of unique and universal goods identifiers in such goods, as may be necessary,`
  line `to prevent unfair trade practices and to protect consumers' interest;`
  line
  line `(j) issue safety notices to alert consumers against dangerous or hazardous or unsafe goods or`
  line services;
  line
  line `(k) advise the Ministries and Departments of the Central and State Governments on consumer`
  line `welfare measures;`
  line
  line `(l) issue necessary guidelines to prevent unfair trade practices and protect consumers' interest.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (50044)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power of Central Authority to refer matter for investigation or to other Regulator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50044&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Central Authority may, after receiving any information or complaint or directions from the Central`
  line `Government or of its own motion, conduct or cause to be conducted a preliminary inquiry as to whether`
  line `there exists a prima facie case of violation of consumer rights or any unfair trade practice or any false or`
  line `misleading advertisement, by any person, which is prejudicial to the public interest or to the interests of`
  line `consumers and if it is satisfied that there exists a prima facie case, it shall cause investigation to be made`
  line `by the Director-General or by the District Collector.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, after preliminary inquiry, the Central Authority is of the opinion that the matter is to be`
  line `dealt with by a Regulator established under any other law for the time being in force, it may refer such`
  line `matter to the concerned Regulator along with its report.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of investigation under sub-section (1), the Central Authority, the Director`
  line `General or the District Collector may call upon a person referred to in sub-section (1) and also direct him`
  line `to produce any document or record in his possession.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (50045)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Power of Central Authority to recall goods, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50045&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Where the Central Authority is satisfied on`
  line `the basis of investigation that there is sufficient evidence to show violation of consumer rights or unfair`
  line `trade practice by a person, it may pass such order as may be necessary, including--`
  line
  line `(a) recalling of goods or withdrawal of services which are dangerous, hazardous or unsafe;`
  line
  line `(b) reimbursement of the prices of goods or services so recalled to purchasers of such goods or`
  line `services; and`
  line
  line `(c) discontinuation of practices which are unfair and prejudicial to consumers' interest:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Authority shall give the person an opportunity of being heard before passing`
  line `an order under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (50136)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Power of Central Authority to issue directions and penalties against false or misleading advertisements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50136&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Central Authority is satisfied after investigation that any advertisement`
  line `is false or misleading and is prejudicial to the interest of any consumer or is in contravention of consumer`
  line `rights, it may, by order, issue directions to the concerned trader or manufacturer or endorser or advertiser or publisher, as the case may be, to discontinue such advertisement or to modify the same in such manner`
  line `and within such time as may be specified in that order.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the order passed under sub-section (1), if the Central Authority is of the opinion`
  line `that it is necessary to impose a penalty in respect of such false or misleading advertisement, by a`
  line `manufacturer or an endorser, it may, by order, impose on manufacturer or endorser a penalty which may`
  line `extend to ten lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Authority may, for every subsequent contravention by a manufacturer or`
  line `endorser, impose a penalty, which may extend to fifty lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding any order under sub-sections (1) and (2), where the Central Authority deems it`
  line `necessary, it may, by order, prohibit the endorser of a false or misleading advertisement from making`
  line `endorsement of any product or service for a period which may extend to one year:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Authority may, for every subsequent contravention, prohibit such endorser`
  line `from making endorsement in respect of any product or service for a period which may extend to three`
  line years.
  line
  line `(4) Where the Central Authority is satisfied after investigation that any person is found to publish, or`
  line `is a party to the publication of, a misleading advertisement, it may impose on such person a penalty which`
  line `may extend to ten lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(5) No endorser shall be liable to a penalty under sub-sections (2) and (3) if he has exercised due`
  line `diligence to verify the veracity of the claims made in the advertisement regarding the product or service`
  line `being endorsed by him.`
  line
  line `(6) No person shall be liable to such penalty if he proves that he had published or arranged for the`
  line `publication of such advertisement in the ordinary course of his business:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such defence shall be available to such person if he had previous knowledge of the`
  line `order passed by the Central Authority for withdrawal or modification of such advertisement.`
  line
  line `(7) While determining the penalty under this section, regard shall be had to the following, namely: --`
  line
  line `(a) the population and the area impacted or affected by such offence;`
  line
  line `(b) the frequency and duration of such offence;`
  line
  line `(c) the vulnerability of the class of persons likely to be adversely affected by such offence; and`
  line
  line `(d) the gross revenue from the sales effected by virtue of such offence.`
  line
  line `(8) The Central Authority shall give the person an opportunity of being heard before an order under`
  line `this section is passed.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (50047)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Search and seizure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50047&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of conducting an investigation after preliminary`
  line `inquiry under sub-section (1) of section 19, the Director-General or any other officer authorised by him in`
  line `this behalf, or the District Collector, as the case may be, may, if he has any reason to believe that any`
  line `person has violated any consumer rights or committed unfair trade practice or causes any false or`
  line `misleading advertisement to be made, shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) enter at any reasonable time into any such premises and search for any document or record or`
  line `article or any other form of evidence and seize such document, record, article or such evidence;`
  line
  line `(b) make a note or an inventory of such record or article; or`
  line
  line `(c) require any person to produce any record, register or other document or article.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), relating to search and seizure`
  line `shall apply, as far as may be, for search and seizure under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Every document, record or article seized under clause (a) of sub-section (1) or produced under`
  line `clause (c) of that sub-section shall be returned to the person, from whom they were seized or who`
  line `produced the same, within a period of twenty days of the date of such seizure or production, as the case may be, after copies thereof or extracts therefrom certified by that person, in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed, have been taken.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any article seized under sub-section (1) are subject to speedy or natural decay, the`
  line `Director-General or such other officer may dispose of the article in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) In the case of articles other than the articles referred to in sub-section (4), provisions contained in`
  line `clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 38 shall mutatis mutandis apply in relation to analysis or tests.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (50048)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Designation of any statutory authority or body to function as Central Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50048&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line The
  line `Central Government may, if it considers necessary, by notification, designate any statutory authority or`
  line `body to exercise the powers and perform the functions of the Central Authority referred to in section 10.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (50049)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50049&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `A person aggrieved by any order passed by the Central Authority under sections 20 and`
  line `21 may file an appeal to the National Commission within a period of thirty days from the date of receipt`
  line `of such order.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (50050)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Grants by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50050&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due appropriation made`
  line `by Parliament by law in this behalf, make to the Central Authority grants of such sums of money as that`
  line `Government may think fit for being utilised for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (50051)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50051&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Authority shall maintain proper accounts and other`
  line `relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form and manner as may be`
  line `prescribed in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Central Authority shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of`
  line `India at such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with such`
  line `audit shall be payable by the Central Authority to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any other person appointed by him in`
  line `connection with the audit of the accounts of the Central Authority shall have the same rights, privileges`
  line `and authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India generally`
  line `has, in connection with the audit of the Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to`
  line `demand the production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to`
  line `inspect any of the offices of the Central Authority.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Central Authority as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of`
  line `India or any other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be`
  line `forwarded annually to the Central Government which shall cause the same to be laid before each House`
  line `of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (50052)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Furnishing of annual reports, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50052&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Authority shall prepare once in every year,`
  line `in such form, manner and at such time as may be prescribed, an annual report giving full account of its`
  line `activities during the previous year and such other reports and returns, as may be directed, and copies of`
  line `such report and returns shall be forwarded to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of the annual report received under sub-section (1) shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is received, before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (50053)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Establishment of District Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50053&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State`
  line `Government shall, by notification, establish a District Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission, to be`
  line `known as the District Commission, in each district of the State:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may, if it deems fit, establish more than one District Commission`
  line `in a district.`
  line
  line `(2) Each District Commission shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) a President; and`
  line
  line `(b) not less than two and not more than such number of members as may be prescribed, in`
  line `consultation with the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (50054)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Qualifications, etc., of President and members of District Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50054&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, make rules to provide for the qualifications, method of recruitment,`
  line `procedure for appointment, term of office, resignation and removal of the President and members of the`
  line `District Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (50135)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Salaries, allowances and other terms and conditions of service of President and members of District Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50135&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, by notification, make rules to provide for salaries`
  line `and allowances and other terms and conditions of service of the President, and members of the District`
  line Commission.
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (50056)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Transitional provision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50056&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Any person appointed as President or, as the case may be, a member of`
  line `the District Commission immediately before the commencement of this Act shall hold office as such as`
  line `President or, as the case may be, as member till the completion of his term for which he has been`
  line appointed.
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (50057)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Vacancy in office of member of District Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50057&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `If, at any time, there is a vacancy in the`
  line `office of the President or member of a District Commission, the State Government may, by notification,`
  line direct--
  line
  line `(a) any other District Commission specified in that notification to exercise the jurisdiction in`
  line `respect of that district also; or`
  line
  line `(b) the President or a member of any other District Commission specified in that notification to`
  line `exercise the powers and discharge the functions of the President or member of that District`
  line `Commission also.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (50058)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Officers and other employees of District Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50058&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall`
  line `provide the District Commission with such officers and other employees as may be required to assist the`
  line `District Commission in the discharge of its functions.`
  line
  line `(2) The officers and other employees of the District Commission shall discharge their functions under`
  line `the general superintendence of the President of the District Commission.`
  line
  line `(3) The salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `officers and other employees of the District Commission shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (50059)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Jurisdiction of District Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50059&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, the`
  line `District Commission shall have jurisdiction to entertain complaints where the value of the goods or`
  line `services paid as consideration does not exceed one crore rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Central Government deems it necessary so to do, it may prescribe such other`
  line `value, as it deems fit.`
  line
  line `(2) A complaint shall be instituted in a District Commission within the local limits of whose`
  line jurisdiction,--
  line
  line `(a) the opposite party or each of the opposite parties, where there are more than one, at the time`
  line `of the institution of the complaint, ordinarily resides or carries on business or has a branch office or`
  line `personally works for gain; or`
  line
  line `(b) any of the opposite parties, where there are more than one, at the time of the institution of the`
  line `complaint, actually and voluntarily resides, or carries on business or has a branch office, or personally`
  line `works for gain, provided that in such case the permission of the District Commission is given; or`
  line
  line `(c) the cause of action, wholly or in part, arises; or`
  line
  line `(d) the complainant resides or personally works for gain.`
  line
  line `(3) The District Commission shall ordinarily function in the district headquarters and may perform its`
  line `functions at such other place in the district, as the State Government may, in consultation with the State`
  line `Commission, notify in the Official Gazette from time to time.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (50060)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Manner in which complaint shall be made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50060&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) A complaint, in relation to any goods sold or`
  line `delivered or agreed to be sold or delivered or any service provided or agreed to be provided, may be filed`
  line `with a District Commission by--`
  line
  line `(a) the consumer,--`
  line
  line `(i) to whom such goods are sold or delivered or agreed to be sold or delivered or such service`
  line `is provided or agreed to be provided; or`
  line
  line `(ii) who alleges unfair trade practice in respect of such goods or service;`
  line
  line `(b) any recognised consumer association, whether the consumer to whom such goods are sold or`
  line `delivered or agreed to be sold or delivered or such service is provided or agreed to be provided, or`
  line `who alleges unfair trade practice in respect of such goods or service, is a member of such association`
  line `or not;`
  line
  line `(c) one or more consumers, where there are numerous consumers having the same interest, with`
  line `the permission of the District Commission, on behalf of, or for the benefit of, all consumers so`
  line `interested; or`
  line
  line `(d) the Central Government, the Central Authority or the State Government, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that the complaint under this sub-section may be filed electronically in such manner as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, "recognised consumer association" means any`
  line `voluntary consumer association registered under any law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(2) Every complaint filed under sub-section (1) shall be accompanied with such fee and payable in`
  line `such manner, including electronic form, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (50061)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Proceedings before District Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50061&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every proceeding before the District`
  line `Commission shall be conducted by the President of that Commission and atleast one member thereof,`
  line `sitting together:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a member, for any reason, is unable to conduct a proceeding till it is completed,`
  line `the President and the other member shall continue the proceeding from the stage at which it was last heard`
  line `by the previous member.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of a complaint made under section 35, the District Commission may, by order, admit`
  line `the complaint for being proceeded with or reject the same:`
  line
  line `Provided that a complaint shall not be rejected under this section unless an opportunity of being heard`
  line `has been given to the complainant:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the admissibility of the complaint shall ordinarily be decided within twenty-one`
  line `days from the date on which the complaint was filed.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the District Commission does not decide the issue of admissibility of the complaint within`
  line `the period so specified, it shall be deemed to have been admitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (50062)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Reference to mediation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50062&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) At the first hearing of the complaint after its admission, or at any`
  line `later stage, if it appears to the District Commission that there exists elements of a settlement which may`
  line `be acceptable to the parties, except in such cases as may be prescribed, it may direct the parties to give in`
  line `writing, within five days, consent to have their dispute settled by mediation in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of Chapter V.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the parties agree for settlement by mediation and give their consent in writing, the District`
  line `Commission shall, within five days of receipt of such consent, refer the matter for mediation, and in such`
  line `case, the provisions of Chapter V, relating to mediation, shall apply`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (50063)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Procedure on admission of complaint.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50063&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The District Commission shall, on admission of a`
  line `complaint, or in respect of cases referred for mediation on failure of settlement by mediation, proceed`
  line `with such complaint.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the complaint relates to any goods, the District Commission shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) refer a copy of the admitted complaint, within twenty-one days from the date of its admission`
  line `to the opposite party mentioned in the complaint directing him to give his version of the case within a`
  line `period of thirty days or such extended period not exceeding fifteen days as may be granted by it;`
  line
  line `(b) if the opposite party on receipt of a complaint referred to him under clause (a) denies or`
  line `disputes the allegations contained in the complaint, or omits or fails to take any action to represent his`
  line `case within the time given by the District Commission, proceed to settle the consumer dispute in the`
  line `manner specified in clauses (c) to (g);`
  line
  line `(c) if the complaint alleges a defect in the goods which cannot be determined without proper`
  line `analysis or test of the goods, obtain a sample of the goods from the complainant, seal it and`
  line `authenticate it in the manner as may be prescribed and refer the sample so sealed to the appropriate`
  line `laboratory along with a direction that such laboratory to make an analysis or test, whichever may be`
  line `necessary, with a view to finding out whether such goods suffer from any defect alleged in the`
  line `complaint or from any other defect and to report its findings thereon to the District Commission`
  line `within a period of forty-five days of the receipt of the reference or within such extended period as`
  line `may be granted by it;`
  line
  line `(d) before any sample of the goods is referred to any appropriate laboratory under clause (c),`
  line `require the complainant to deposit to the credit of the Commission such fees as may be specified, for`
  line `payment to the appropriate laboratory for carrying out the necessary analysis or test in relation to the`
  line `goods in question;`
  line
  line `(e) remit the amount deposited to its credit under clause (d) to the appropriate laboratory to enable`
  line `it to carry out the analysis or test mentioned in clause (c) and on receipt of the report from the`
  line `appropriate laboratory, it shall forward a copy of the report along with such remarks as it may feel`
  line `appropriate to the opposite party;`
  line
  line `(f) if any of the parties disputes the correctness of the findings of the appropriate laboratory, or`
  line `disputes the correctness of the methods of analysis or test adopted by the appropriate laboratory,`
  line `require the opposite party or the complainant to submit in writing his objections with regard to the`
  line `report made by the appropriate laboratory;`
  line
  line `(g) give a reasonable opportunity to the complainant as well as the opposite party of being heard`
  line `as to the correctness or otherwise of the report made by the appropriate laboratory and also as to the`
  line `objection made in relation thereto under clause (f) and issue an appropriate order under section 39.`
  line
  line `(3) The District Commission shall, if the complaint admitted by it under sub-section (2) of section 36`
  line `relates to goods in respect of which the procedure specified in sub-section (2) cannot be followed, or if`
  line `the complaint relates to any services,--`
  line
  line `(a) refer a copy of such complaint to the opposite party directing him to give his version of the`
  line `case within a period of thirty days or such extended period not exceeding fifteen days as may be`
  line `granted by the District Commission;`
  line
  line `(b) if the opposite party, on receipt of a copy of the complaint, referred to him under clause (a)`
  line `denies or disputes the allegations contained in the complaint, or omits or fails to take any action to`
  line `represent his case within the time given by the District Commission, it shall proceed to settle the`
  line `consumer dispute--`
  line
  line `(i) on the basis of evidence brought to its notice by the complainant and the opposite party, if`
  line `the opposite party denies or disputes the allegations contained in the complaint, or`
  line
  line `(ii) ex parte on the basis of evidence brought to its notice by the complainant, where the`
  line `opposite party omits or fails to take any action to represent his case within the time given by the`
  line Commission;
  line
  line `(c) decide the complaint on merits if the complainant fails to appear on the date of hearing.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of sub-sections (2) and (3), the District Commission may, by order, require an`
  line `electronic service provider to provide such information, documents or records, as may be specified in that`
  line order.
  line
  line `(5) No proceedings complying with the procedure laid down in [sub-sections (2) and (3)] shall be`
  line `called in question in any court on the ground that the principles of natural justice have not been complied`
  line with.
  line
  line `(6) Every complaint shall be heard by the District Commission on the basis of affidavit and`
  line `documentary evidence placed on record:`
  line
  line `Provided that where an application is made for hearing or for examination of parties in person or`
  line `through video conferencing, the District Commission may, on sufficient cause being shown, and after`
  line `recording its reasons in writing, allow the same.`
  line
  line `(7) Every complaint shall be disposed of as expeditiously as possible and endeavour shall be made to`
  line `decide the complaint within a period of three months from the date of receipt of notice by opposite party`
  line `where the complaint does not require analysis or testing of commodities and within five months if it`
  line `requires analysis or testing of commodities:`
  line
  line `Provided that no adjournment shall ordinarily be granted by the District Commission unless sufficient`
  line `cause is shown and the reasons for grant of adjournment have been recorded in writing by the`
  line `Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the District Commission shall make such orders as to the costs occasioned by`
  line `the adjournment as may be specified by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided also that in the event of a complaint being disposed of after the period so specified, the`
  line `District Commission shall record in writing, the reasons for the same at the time of disposing of the said`
  line complaint.
  line
  line `(8) Where during the pendency of any proceeding before the District Commission, if it appears`
  line `necessary, it may pass such interim order as is just and proper in the facts and circumstances of the case.`
  line
  line `(9) For the purposes of this section, the District Commission shall have the same powers as are vested`
  line `in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) while trying a suit in respect of the`
  line `following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the summoning and enforcing the attendance of any defendant or witness and examining the`
  line `witness on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of any document or other material object as evidence;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving of evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) the requisitioning of the report of the concerned analysis or test from the appropriate`
  line `laboratory or from any other relevant source;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing of commissions for the examination of any witness, or document; and`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(10) Every proceeding before the District Commission shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding`
  line `within the meaning of section 193 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), and the District`
  line `Commission shall be deemed to be a criminal court for the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXVI of`
  line `the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `(11) Where the complainant is a consumer referred to in sub-clause (v) of clause (5) of section 2, the`
  line `provisions of Order I Rule 8 of the First Schedule to the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) shall`
  line `apply subject to the modification that every reference therein to a suit or decree shall be construed as a`
  line `reference to a complaint or the order of the District Commission thereon.`
  line
  line `(12) In the event of death of a complainant who is a consumer or of the opposite party against whom`
  line `the complaint has been filed, the provisions of Order XXII of the First Schedule to the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) shall apply subject to the modification that every reference therein to the`
  line `plaintiff and the defendant shall be construed as reference to a complainant or the opposite party, as the`
  line `case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (50064)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Findings of District Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50064&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the District Commission is satisfied that the`
  line `goods complained against suffer from any of the defects specified in the complaint or that any of the`
  line `allegations contained in the complaint about the services or any unfair trade practices, or claims for`
  line `compensation under product liability are proved, it shall issue an order to the opposite party directing him`
  line `to do one or more of the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) to remove the defect pointed out by the appropriate laboratory from the goods in question;`
  line
  line `(b) to replace the goods with new goods of similar description which shall be free from any`
  line defect;
  line
  line `(c) to return to the complainant the price, or, as the case may be, the charges paid by the`
  line `complainant along with such interest on such price or charges as may be decided;`
  line
  line `(d) to pay such amount as may be awarded by it as compensation to the consumer for any loss or`
  line `injury suffered by the consumer due to the negligence of the opposite party:`
  line
  line `Provided that the District Commission shall have the power to grant punitive damages in such`
  line `circumstances as it deems fit;`
  line
  line `(e) to pay such amount as may be awarded by it as compensation in a product liability action`
  line `under Chapter VI;`
  line
  line `(f) to remove the defects in goods or deficiencies in the services in question;`
  line
  line `(g) to discontinue the unfair trade practice or restrictive trade practice and not to repeat them;`
  line
  line `(h) not to offer the hazardous or unsafe goods for sale;`
  line
  line `(i) to withdraw the hazardous goods from being offered for sale;`
  line
  line `(j) to cease manufacture of hazardous goods and to desist from offering services which are`
  line `hazardous in nature;`
  line
  line `(k) to pay such sum as may be determined by it, if it is of the opinion that loss or injury has been`
  line `suffered by a large number of consumers who are not identifiable conveniently:`
  line
  line `Provided that the minimum amount of sum so payable shall not be less than twenty-five per cent.`
  line `of the value of such defective goods sold or service provided, as the case may be, to such consumers;`
  line
  line `(l) to issue corrective advertisement to neutralise the effect of misleading advertisement at the`
  line `cost of the opposite party responsible for issuing such misleading advertisement;`
  line
  line `(m) to provide for adequate costs to parties; and`
  line
  line `(n) to cease and desist from issuing any misleading advertisement.`
  line
  line `(2) Any amount obtained under sub-section (1) shall be credited to such fund and utilised in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) In any proceeding conducted by the President and a member and if they differ on any point or`
  line `points, they shall state the point or points on which they differ and refer the same to another member for`
  line `hearing on such point or points and the opinion of the majority shall be the order of the District`
  line `Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided that the other member shall give his opinion on such point or points referred to him within a`
  line `period of one month from the date of such reference.`
  line
  line `(4) Every order made by the District Commission under sub-section (1) shall be signed by the`
  line `President and the member who conducted the proceeding:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the order is made as per majority opinion under sub-section (3), such order shall`
  line `also be signed by the other member.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (50065)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Review by District Commission in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50065&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `The District Commission shall have the`
  line `power to review any of the order passed by it if there is an error apparent on the face of the record, either`
  line `of its own motion or on an application made by any of the parties within thirty days of such order.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (50066)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Appeal against order of District Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50066&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `Any person aggrieved by an order made by the`
  line `District Commission may prefer an appeal against such order to the State Commission on the grounds of`
  line `facts or law within a period of forty-five days from the date of the order, in such form and manner, as may`
  line `be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Commission may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `forty-five days, if it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not filing it within that period:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no appeal by a person, who is required to pay any amount in terms of an order of`
  line `the District Commission, shall be entertained by the State Commission unless the appellant has deposited`
  line `fifty per cent. of that amount in the manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided also that no appeal shall lie from any order passed under sub-section (1) of section 81 by the`
  line `District Commission pursuant to a settlement by mediation under section 80.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (50067)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Establishment of State Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50067&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State`
  line `Government shall, by notification, establish a State Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission, to be`
  line `known as the State Commission, in the State.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Commission shall ordinarily function at the State capital and perform its functions at`
  line `such other places as the State Government may in consultation with the State Commission notify in the`
  line `Official Gazette:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may, by notification, establish regional benches of the State`
  line `Commission, at such places, as it deems fit.`
  line
  line `(3) Each State Commission shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) a President; and`
  line
  line `(b) not less than four or not more than such number of members as may be prescribed in`
  line `consultation with the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (50068)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Qualifications, etc., of President and members of State Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50068&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `The Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, make rules to provide for the qualification for appointment, method of`
  line `recruitment, procedure of appointment, term of office, resignation and removal of the President and`
  line `members of the State Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (50137)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Salaries, allowances and other terms and conditions of service of President and members of State Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50137&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, by notification, make rules to provide for salaries and`
  line `allowances and other terms and conditions of service of the President and members of the State`
  line Commission.
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (50070)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Transitional provision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50070&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Any person appointed as President or, as the case may be, a member of`
  line `the State Commission immediately before the commencement of this Act shall hold office as such, as`
  line `President or member, as the case may be, till the completion of his term.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (50071)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Officers and employees of State Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50071&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall determine the`
  line `nature and categories of the officers and other employees required to assist the State Commission in the`
  line `discharge of its functions and provide the Commission with such officers and other employees as it may`
  line `think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The officers and other employees of the State Commission shall discharge their functions under`
  line `the general superintendence of the President.`
  line
  line `(3) The salaries and allowances payable to and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `officers and other employees of the State Commission shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (50072)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Jurisdiction of State Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50072&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, the State`
  line `Commission shall have jurisdiction--`
  line
  line `(a) to entertain--`
  line
  line `(i) complaints where the value of the goods or services paid as consideration, exceeds rupees`
  line `one crore, but does not exceed rupees ten crore:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Central Government deems it necessary so to do, it may prescribe`
  line `such other value, as it deems fit;`
  line
  line `(ii) complaints against unfair contracts, where the value of goods or services paid as`
  line `consideration does not exceed ten crore rupees;`
  line
  line `(iii) appeals against the orders of any District Commission within the State; and`
  line
  line `(b) to call for the records and pass appropriate orders in any consumer dispute which is pending`
  line `before or has been decided by any District Commission within the State, where it appears to the State`
  line `Commission that such District Commission has exercised a jurisdiction not vested in it by law, or has`
  line `failed to exercise a jurisdiction so vested or has acted in exercise of its jurisdiction illegally or with`
  line `material irregularity.`
  line
  line `(2) The jurisdiction, powers and authority of the State Commission may be exercised by Benches`
  line `thereof, and a Bench may be constituted by the President with one or more members as the President may`
  line `deem fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the senior-most member shall preside over the Bench.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the members of a Bench differ in opinion on any point, the points shall be decided`
  line `according to the opinion of the majority, if there is a majority, but if the members are equally divided,`
  line `they shall state the point or points on which they differ, and make a reference to the President who shall`
  line `either hear the point or points himself or refer the case for hearing on such point or points by one or more`
  line `of the other members and such point or points shall be decided according to the opinion of the majority of`
  line `the members who have heard the case, including those who first heard it:`
  line
  line `Provided that the President or the other members, as the case may be, shall give opinion on the point`
  line `or points so referred within a period of one month from the date of such reference.`
  line
  line `(4) A complaint shall be instituted in a State Commission within the limits of whose jurisdiction,--`
  line
  line `(a) the opposite party or each of the opposite parties, where there are more than one, at the time`
  line `of the institution of the complaint, ordinarily resides or carries on business or has a branch office or`
  line `personally works for gain; or`
  line
  line `(b) any of the opposite parties, where there are more than one, at the time of the institution of`
  line `the complaint, actually and voluntarily resides, or carries on business or has a branch office or`
  line `personally works for gain, provided in such case, the permission of the State Commission is given;`
  line or
  line
  line `(c) the cause of action, wholly or in part, arises; or`
  line
  line `(d) the complainant resides or personally works for gain.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (50073)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Transfer of cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50073&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `On the application of the complainant or of its own motion, the State`
  line `Commission may, at any stage of the proceeding, transfer any complaint pending before a District`
  line `Commission to another District Commission within the State if the interest of justice so requires.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (50074)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Procedure applicable to State Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50074&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions relating to complaints under`
  line `sections 35, 36, 37, 38 and 39 shall, with such modifications as may be necessary, be applicable to the`
  line `disposal of complaints by the State Commission.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the State Commission may also declare any`
  line `terms of contract, which is unfair to any consumer, to be null and void.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (50075)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Review by State Commission in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50075&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `The State Commission shall have the power to`
  line `review any of the order passed by it if there is an error apparent on the face of the record, either of its own`
  line `motion or on an application made by any of the parties within thirty days of such order.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (50076)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Appeal to National Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50076&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an order made by the State`
  line `Commission in exercise of its powers conferred by sub-clause (i) or (ii) of clause (a) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 47 may prefer an appeal against such order to the National Commission within a period of thirty`
  line `days from the date of the order in such form and manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the National Commission shall not entertain the appeal after the expiry of the said`
  line `period of thirty days unless it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not filing it within that period:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no appeal by a person, who is required to pay any amount in terms of an order of`
  line `the State Commission, shall be entertained by the National Commission unless the appellant has`
  line `deposited fifty per cent. of that amount in the manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise expressly provided under this Act or by any other law for the time being in`
  line `force, an appeal shall lie to the National Commission from any order passed in appeal by any State`
  line `Commission, if the National Commission is satisfied that the case involves a substantial question of law.`
  line
  line `(3) In an appeal involving a question of law, the memorandum of appeal shall precisely state the`
  line `substantial question of law involved in the appeal.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the National Commission is satisfied that a substantial question of law is involved in any`
  line `case, it shall formulate that question and hear the appeal on that question:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall be deemed to take away or abridge the power of the`
  line `National Commission to hear, for reasons to be recorded in writing, the appeal on any other substantial`
  line `question of law, if it is satisfied that the case involves such question of law.`
  line
  line `(5) An appeal may lie to the National Commission under this section from an order passed ex parte`
  line `by the State Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (50077)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Hearing of appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50077&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `An appeal filed before the State Commission or the National Commission,`
  line `as the case may be, shall be heard as expeditiously as possible and every endeavour shall be made to`
  line `dispose of the appeal within a period of ninety days from the date of its admission:`
  line
  line `Provided that no adjournment shall ordinarily be granted by the State Commission or the National`
  line `Commission, as the case may be, unless sufficient cause is shown and the reasons for grant of`
  line `adjournment have been recorded in writing by such Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the State Commission or the National Commission, as the case may be, shall`
  line `make such orders as to the costs occasioned by the adjournment, as may be specified by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided also that in the event of an appeal being disposed of after the period so specified, the State`
  line `Commission or the National Commission, as the case may be, shall record in writing the reasons for the`
  line `same at the time of disposing of the said appeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (50078)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Establishment of National Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50078&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government shall, by notification, establish a National Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission, to be`
  line `known as the National Commission.`
  line
  line `(2) The National Commission shall ordinarily function at the National Capital Region and perform its`
  line `functions at such other places as the Central Government may in consultation with the National`
  line `Commission notify in the Official Gazette:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, by notification, establish regional Benches of the`
  line `National Commission, at such places, as it deems fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (50079)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Composition of National Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50079&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `The National Commission shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) a President; and`
  line
  line `(b) not less than four and not more than such number of members as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (50080)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Qualifications, etc., of President and members of National Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 30 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50080&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, make rules to provide for qualifications, appointment, term of office,`
  line `salaries and allowances, resignation, removal and other terms and conditions of service of the President`
  line `and members of the National Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided that the President and members of the National Commission shall hold office for such term`
  line `as specified in the rules made by the Central Government but not exceeding five years from the date on`
  line `which he enters upon his office and shall be eligible for re-appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no President or members shall hold office as such after he has attained such age`
  line `as specified in the rules made by the Central Government which shall not exceed,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of the President, the age of seventy years;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of any other member, the age of sixty-seven years.`
  line
  line `^1[(1A) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the qualifications, appointment, term of`
  line `office, salaries and allowances, resignation, removal and the other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `President and other members of the National Commission appointed after the commencement of the`
  line `Tribunal Reforms Act, 2021, shall be governed by the provisions of the said Act.]`
  line
  line `(2) Neither the salary and allowances nor the other terms and conditions of service of President and`
  line `members of the National Commission shall be varied to his disadvantage after his appointment.`
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (50081)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Transitional provision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50081&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `The President and every other member appointed immediately before`
  line `the commencement of section 177 of the Finance Act, 2017 (7 of 2017) shall continue to be governed by`
  line `the provisions of the Consumer Protection Act, 1986 (68 of 1986) and the rules made there under as if`
  line `this Act had not come into force.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (50082)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Other officers and employees of National Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50082&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall`
  line `provide, in consultation with the President of the National Commission, such number of officers and other`
  line `employees to assist the National Commission in the discharge of its functions as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The officers and other employees of the National Commission shall discharge their functions`
  line `under the general superintendence of the President of the National Commission.`
  line
  line `(3) The salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `officers and other employees of the National Commission shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (50083)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Jurisdiction of National Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50083&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, the`
  line `National Commission shall have jurisdiction--`
  line
  line `(a) to entertain--`
  line
  line `(i) complaints where the value of the goods or services paid as consideration exceeds rupees`
  line `ten crore:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Central Government deems it necessary so to do, it may prescribe`
  line `such other value, as it deems fit;`
  line
  line `(ii) complaints against unfair contracts, where the value of goods or services paid as`
  line `consideration exceeds ten crore rupees;`
  line
  line `(iii) appeals against the orders of any State Commission;`
  line
  line `(iv) appeals against the orders of the Central Authority; and`
  line
  line `(b) to call for the records and pass appropriate orders in any consumer dispute which is pending`
  line `before or has been decided by any State Commission where it appears to the National Commission`
  line `that such State Commission has exercised a jurisdiction not vested in it by law, or has failed to`
  line `exercise a jurisdiction so vested, or has acted in the exercise of its jurisdiction illegally or with`
  line `material irregularity.`
  line
  line `(2) The jurisdiction, powers and authority of the National Commission may be exercised by Benches`
  line `thereof and a Bench may be constituted by the President with one or more members as he may deem fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the senior-most member of the Bench shall preside over the Bench.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the members of a Bench differ in opinion on any point, the points shall be decided`
  line `according to the opinion of the majority, if there is a majority, but if the members are equally divided, they shall state the point or points on which they differ, and make a reference to the President who shall`
  line `either hear the point or points himself or refer the case for hearing on such point or points by one or more`
  line `of the other members and such point or points shall be decided according to the opinion of the majority of`
  line `the members who have heard the case, including those who first heard it:`
  line
  line `Provided that the President or the other member, as the case may be, shall give opinion on the point or`
  line `points so referred within a period of two months from the date of such reference.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (50084)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Procedure applicable to National Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50084&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions relating to complaints`
  line `under sections 35, 36, 37, 38 and 39 shall, with such modifications as may be considered necessary, be`
  line `applicable to the disposal of complaints by the National Commission.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to sub-section (1), the National Commission may also declare any terms of`
  line `contract, which is unfair to any consumer to be null and void.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (50085)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Review by National Commission in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50085&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `The National Commission shall have the`
  line `power to review any of the order passed by it if there is an error apparent on the face of the record, either`
  line `of its own motion or on an application made by any of the parties within thirty days of such order.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (50086)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Power to set aside ex parte orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50086&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `Where an order is passed by the National Commission ex`
  line `parte, the aggrieved party may make an application to the Commission for setting aside such order.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (50087)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Transfer of cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50087&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `On the application of the complainant or of its own motion, the National`
  line `Commission may, at any stage of the proceeding, in the interest of justice, transfer any complaint pending`
  line `before the District Commission of one State to a District Commission of another State or before one State`
  line `Commission to another State Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (50088)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Vacancy in office of President of National Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50088&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `When the office of President of the`
  line `National Commission is vacant or a person occupying such office is, by reason of absence or otherwise,`
  line `unable to perform the duties of his office, these shall be performed by the senior-most member of the`
  line `National Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a retired Judge of a High Court or a person who has been a Judicial Member is a`
  line `member of the National Commission, such member or where the number of such members is more than`
  line `one, the senior-most person amongst such members, shall preside over the National Commission in the`
  line `absence of President of that Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (50089)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Vacancies or defects in appointment not to invalidate orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50089&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of the`
  line `District Commission, the State Commission or the National Commission shall be invalid by reason only`
  line `of the existence of any vacancy amongst its members or any defect in the constitution thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (50090)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Service of notice, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50090&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) All notices, required by this Act to be served, shall be served by`
  line `delivering or transmitting a copy thereof by registered post acknowledgment due addressed to opposite`
  line `party against whom complaint is made or to the complainant by speed post or by such courier service,`
  line `approved by the District Commission, the State Commission or the National Commission, as the case`
  line `may be, or by any other mode of transmission of documents including electronic means.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section (1), the notice required by this Act`
  line `may be served on an electronic service provider at the address provided by it on the electronic platform`
  line `from where it provides its services as such and for this purpose, the electronic service provider shall`
  line `designate a nodal officer to accept and process such notices.`
  line
  line `(3) When an acknowledgment or any other receipt purporting to be signed by the opposite party or his`
  line `agent or, as the case may be, by the complainant is received by the District Commission, the State`
  line `Commission or the National Commission, as the case may be, or postal article containing the notice is`
  line `received back by such District Commission, State Commission or the National Commission, with an`
  line `endorsement purporting to have been made by a postal employee or by any person authorised by the`
  line `courier service to the effect that the opposite party or his agent or complainant had refused to take`
  line `delivery of the postal article containing the notice or had refused to accept the notice by any other means`
  line `specified in sub-section (1) when tendered or transmitted to him, the District Commission or the State Commission or the National Commission, as the case may be, shall declare that the notice has been duly`
  line `served on the opposite party or to the complainant, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the notice was properly addressed, pre-paid and duly sent by registered post`
  line `acknowledgment due, a declaration referred to in this sub-section shall be made notwithstanding the fact`
  line `that the acknowledgment has been lost or misplaced, or for any other reason, has not been received by the`
  line `District Commission, the State Commission or the National Commission, as the case may be, within`
  line `thirty days from the date of issue of notice.`
  line
  line `(4) All notices required to be served on an opposite party or to complainant, as the case may be, shall`
  line `be deemed to be sufficiently served, if addressed in the case of the opposite party, to the place where`
  line `business or profession is carried on, and in case of the complainant, the place where such person actually`
  line `and voluntarily resides.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (50091)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Experts to assist National Commission or State Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50091&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `Where the National`
  line `Commission or the State Commission, as the case may be, on an application by a complainant or`
  line `otherwise, is of the opinion that it involves the larger interest of consumers, it may direct any individual`
  line `or organisation or expert to assist the National Commission or the State Commission, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (50092)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Appeal against order of National Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50092&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `Any person, aggrieved by an order made by`
  line `the National Commission in exercise of its powers conferred by sub-clause (i) or (ii) of clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 58, may prefer an appeal against such order to the Supreme Court within a`
  line `period of thirty days from the date of the order:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Supreme Court may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of thirty`
  line `days if it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not filing it within that period:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no appeal by a person who is required to pay any amount in terms of an order of`
  line `the National Commission shall be entertained by the Supreme Court unless that person has deposited fifty`
  line `per cent. of that amount in the manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (50093)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Finality of orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50093&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `Every order of a District Commission or the State Commission or the`
  line `National Commission, as the case may be, shall, if no appeal has been preferred against such order under`
  line `the provisions of this Act, be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (50094)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Limitation period.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50094&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `(1) The District Commission, the State Commission or the National`
  line `Commission shall not admit a complaint unless it is filed within two years from the date on which the`
  line `cause of action has arisen.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), a complaint may be entertained after the`
  line `period specified in sub-section (1), if the complainant satisfies the District Commission, the State`
  line `Commission or the National Commission, as the case may be, that he had sufficient cause for not filing`
  line `the complaint within such period:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such complaint shall be entertained unless the District Commission or the State`
  line `Commission or the National Commission, as the case may be, records its reasons for condoning such`
  line delay.
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (50095)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Administrative control.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50095&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Commission shall have the authority to lay down`
  line `such adequate standards in consultation with the Central Government from time to time, for better`
  line `protection of the interests of consumers and for that purpose, shall have administrative control over all the`
  line `State Commissions in the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) monitoring performance of the State Commissions in terms of their disposal by calling for`
  line `periodical returns regarding the institution, disposal and pendency of cases;`
  line
  line `(b) investigating into any allegations against the President and members of a State Commission`
  line `and submitting inquiry report to the State Government concerned along with copy endorsed to the`
  line `Central Government for necessary action;`
  line
  line `(c) issuance of instructions regarding adoption of uniform procedure in the hearing of matters,`
  line `prior service of copies of documents produced by one party to the opposite parties, furnishing of`
  line `english translation of judgments written in any language, speedy grant of copies of documents;`
  line
  line `(d) overseeing the functioning of the State Commission or the District Commission either by way`
  line `of inspection or by any other means, as the National Commission may like to order from time to time,`
  line `to ensure that the objects and purposes of the Act are best served and the standards set by the National`
  line `Commission are implemented without interfering with their quasi-judicial freedom.`
  line
  line `(2) There shall be a monitoring cell to be constituted by the President of the National Commission to`
  line `oversee the functioning of the State Commissions from the administrative point of view.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Commission shall have administrative control over all the District Commissions within`
  line `its jurisdiction in all matters referred to in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) The National Commission and the State Commissions shall furnish to the Central Government`
  line `periodically or as and when required, any information including the pendency of cases in such form and`
  line `manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) The State Commission shall furnish, periodically or as and when required to the State Government`
  line `any information including pendency of cases in such form and manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (50096)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Enforcement of orders of District Commission, State Commission and National Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50096&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `Every order made by a District Commission, State Commission or the National`
  line `Commission shall be enforced by it in the same manner as if it were a decree made by a Court in a suit`
  line `before it and the provisions of Order XXI of the First Schedule to the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of`
  line `1908) shall, as far as may be, applicable, subject to the modification that every reference therein to the`
  line `decree shall be construed as reference to the order made under this Act`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (50097)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Penalty for non-compliance of order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50097&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever fails to comply with any order made by the`
  line `District Commission or the State Commission or the National Commission, as the case may be, shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than one month, but which may extend to`
  line `three years, or with fine, which shall not be less than twenty-five thousand rupees, but which may extend`
  line `to one lakh rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), the`
  line `District Commission, the State Commission or the National Commission, as the case may be, shall have`
  line `the power of a Judicial Magistrate of first class for the trial of offences under sub-section (1), and on`
  line `conferment of such powers, the District Commission or the State Commission or the National`
  line `Commission, as the case may be, shall be deemed to be a Judicial Magistrate of first class for the`
  line `purposes of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973.`
  line
  line `(3) Save as otherwise provided, the offences under sub-section (1) shall be tried summarily by the`
  line `District Commission or the State Commission or the National Commission, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (50098)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Appeal against order passed under section 72.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50098&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), where an order is passed under sub-section (1) of section`
  line `72, an appeal shall lie, both on facts and on law from--`
  line
  line `(a) the order made by the District Commission to the State Commission;`
  line
  line `(b) the order made by the State Commission to the National Commission; and`
  line
  line `(c) the order made by the National Commission to the Supreme Court.`
  line
  line `(2) Except as provided in sub-section (1), no appeal shall lie before any court, from any order of a`
  line `District Commission or a State Commission or the National Commission, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) Every appeal under this section shall be preferred within a period of thirty days from the date of`
  line `order of a District Commission or a State Commission or the National Commission, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Commission or the National Commission or the Supreme Court, as the case`
  line `may be, may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of thirty days, if it is satisfied that the`
  line `appellant had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within the said period of thirty days.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (50099)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Establishment of consumer mediation cell.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50099&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall establish, by`
  line `notification, a consumer mediation cell to be attached to each of the District Commissions and the State`
  line `Commissions of that State.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall establish, by notification, a consumer mediation cell to be attached`
  line `to the National Commission and each of the regional Benches.`
  line
  line `(3) A consumer mediation cell shall consist of such persons as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Every consumer mediation cell shall maintain--`
  line
  line `(a) a list of empanelled mediators;`
  line
  line `(b) a list of cases handled by the cell;`
  line
  line `(c) record of proceeding; and`
  line
  line `(d) any other information as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(5) Every consumer mediation cell shall submit a quarterly report to the District Commission, State`
  line `Commission or the National Commission to which it is attached, in the manner specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (50100)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Empanelment of mediators.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50100&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of mediation, the National Commission or the`
  line `State Commission or the District Commission, as the case may be, shall prepare a panel of the mediators`
  line `to be maintained by the consumer mediation cell attached to it, on the recommendation of a selection`
  line `committee consisting of the President and a member of that Commission.`
  line
  line `(2) The qualifications and experience required for empanelment as mediator, the procedure for`
  line `empanelment, the manner of training empanelled mediators, the fee payable to empanelled mediator, the`
  line `terms and conditions for empanelment, the code of conduct for empanelled mediators, the grounds on`
  line `which, and the manner in which, empanelled mediators shall be removed or empanelment shall be`
  line `cancelled and other matters relating thereto, shall be such as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) The panel of mediators prepared under sub-section (1) shall be valid for a period of five years, and`
  line `the empanelled mediators shall be eligible to be considered for re-empanelment for another term, subject`
  line `to such conditions as may be specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (50101)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Nomination of mediators from panel.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50101&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `The District Commission, the State Commission or the`
  line `National Commission shall, while nominating any person from the panel of mediators referred to in`
  line `section 75, consider his suitability for resolving the consumer dispute involved.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (50102)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Duty of mediator to disclose certain facts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50102&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of the mediator to disclose--`
  line
  line `(a) any personal, professional or financial interest in the outcome of the consumer dispute;`
  line
  line `(b) the circumstances which may give rise to a justifiable doubt as to his independence or`
  line `impartiality; and`
  line
  line `(c) such other facts as may be specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (50103)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Replacement of mediator in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50103&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `Where the District Commission or the State`
  line `Commission or the National Commission, as the case may be, is satisfied, on the information furnished by`
  line `the mediator or on the information received from any other person including parties to the complaint and`
  line `after hearing the mediator, it shall replace such mediator by another mediator.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (50104)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Procedure for mediation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50104&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) The mediation shall be held in the consumer mediation cell`
  line `attached to the District Commission, the State Commission or the National Commission, as the case may`
  line be.
  line
  line `(2) Where a consumer dispute is referred for mediation by the District Commission or the State`
  line `Commission or the National Commission, as the case may be, the mediator nominated by such`
  line `Commission shall have regard to the rights and obligations of the parties, the usages of trade, if any, the`
  line `circumstances giving rise to the consumer dispute and such other relevant factors, as he may deem`
  line `necessary and shall be guided by the principles of natural justice while carrying out mediation.`
  line
  line `(3) The mediator so nominated shall conduct mediation within such time and in such manner as may`
  line `be specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (50105)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Settlement through mediation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50105&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `(1) Pursuant to mediation, if an agreement is reached between`
  line `the parties with respect to all of the issues involved in the consumer dispute or with respect to only some`
  line `of the issues, the terms of such agreement shall be reduced to writing accordingly, and signed by the`
  line `parties to such dispute or their authorised representatives.`
  line
  line `(2) The mediator shall prepare a settlement report of the settlement and forward the signed agreement`
  line `along with such report to the concerned Commission.`
  line
  line `(3) Where no agreement is reached between the parties within the specified time or the mediator is of`
  line `the opinion that settlement is not possible, he shall prepare his report accordingly and submit the same to`
  line `the concerned Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (50106)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Recording settlement and passing of order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50106&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `(1) The District Commission or the State`
  line `Commission or the National Commission, as the case may be, shall, within seven days of the receipt of`
  line `the settlement report, pass suitable order recording such settlement of consumer dispute and dispose of the`
  line `matter accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the consumer dispute is settled only in part, the District Commission or the State`
  line `Commission or the National Commission, as the case may be, shall record settlement of the issues which`
  line `have been so settled and continue to hear other issues involved in such consumer dispute.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the consumer dispute could not be settled by mediation, the District Commission or the`
  line `State Commission or the National Commission, as the case may be, shall continue to hear all the issues`
  line `involved in such consumer dispute.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (50107)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Application of Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50107&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `This Chapter shall apply to every claim for compensation under a`
  line `product liability action by a complainant for any harm caused by a defective product manufactured by a`
  line `product manufacturer or serviced by a product service provider or sold by a product seller.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (50134)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Product liability action 84. Liability of product manufacturer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50134&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `A product liability action may be brought by a complainant against a`
  line `product manufacturer or a product service provider or a product seller, as the case may be, for any harm`
  line `caused to him on account of a defective product.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (50139)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Liability of product manufacturer`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50139&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `(1) A product manufacturer shall be liable in a product`
  line `liability action, if--`
  line
  line `(a) the product contains a manufacturing defect; or`
  line
  line `(b) the product is defective in design; or`
  line
  line `(c) there is a deviation from manufacturing specifications; or`
  line
  line `(d) the product does not conform to the express warranty; or`
  line
  line `(e) the product fails to contain adequate instructions of correct usage to prevent any harm or any`
  line `warning regarding improper or incorrect usage.`
  line
  line `(2) A product manufacturer shall be liable in a product liability action even if he proves that he was`
  line `not negligent or fraudulent in making the express warranty of a product.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (50109)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Liability of product service provider.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50109&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `A product service provider shall be liable in a product`
  line `liability action, if--`
  line
  line `(a) the service provided by him was faulty or imperfect or deficient or inadequate in quality, nature or`
  line `manner of performance which is required to be provided by or under any law for the time being in force,`
  line `or pursuant to any contract or otherwise; or`
  line
  line `(b) there was an act of omission or commission or negligence or conscious withholding any`
  line `information which caused harm; or`
  line
  line `(c) the service provider did not issue adequate instructions or warnings to prevent any harm; or`
  line
  line `(d) the service did not conform to express warranty or the terms and conditions of the contract.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (50110)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Liability of product sellers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50110&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `A product seller who is not a product manufacturer shall be liable`
  line `in a product liability action, if--`
  line
  line `(a) he has exercised substantial control over the designing, testing, manufacturing, packaging or`
  line `labelling of a product that caused harm; or`
  line
  line `(b) he has altered or modified the product and such alteration or modification was the substantial`
  line `factor in causing the harm; or`
  line
  line `(c) he has made an express warranty of a product independent of any express warranty made by a`
  line `manufacturer and such product failed to conform to the express warranty made by the product seller`
  line `which caused the harm; or`
  line
  line `(d) the product has been sold by him and the identity of product manufacturer of such product is`
  line `not known, or if known, the service of notice or process or warrant cannot be effected on him or he is`
  line `not subject to the law which is in force in India or the order, if any, passed or to be passed cannot be`
  line `enforced against him; or`
  line
  line `(e) he failed to exercise reasonable care in assembling, inspecting or maintaining such product or`
  line `he did not pass on the warnings or instructions of the product manufacturer regarding the dangers`
  line `involved or proper usage of the product while selling such product and such failure was the proximate`
  line `cause of the harm.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (50111)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Exceptions to product liability action.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50111&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `(1) A product liability action cannot be brought against`
  line `the product seller if, at the time of harm, the product was misused, altered, or modified.`
  line
  line `(2) In any product liability action based on the failure to provide adequate warnings or instructions,`
  line `the product manufacturer shall not be liable, if--`
  line
  line `(a) the product was purchased by an employer for use at the workplace and the product`
  line `manufacturer had provided warnings or instructions to such employer;`
  line
  line `(b) the product was sold as a component or material to be used in another product and necessary`
  line `warnings or instructions were given by the product manufacturer to the purchaser of such component`
  line `or material, but the harm was caused to the complainant by use of the end product in which such`
  line `component or material was used;`
  line
  line `(c) the product was one which was legally meant to be used or dispensed only by or under the`
  line `supervision of an expert or a class of experts and the product manufacturer had employed reasonable`
  line `means to give the warnings or instructions for usage of such product to such expert or class of`
  line `experts; or`
  line
  line `(d) the complainant, while using such product, was under the influence of alcohol or any`
  line `prescription drug which had not been prescribed by a medical practitioner.`
  line
  line `(3) A product manufacturer shall not be liable for failure to instruct or warn about a danger which is`
  line `obvious or commonly known to the user or consumer of such product or which, such user or consumer,`
  line `ought to have known, taking into account the characteristics of such product.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (50112)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Penalty for non-compliance of direction of Central Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50112&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, fails to comply`
  line `with any direction of the Central Authority under sections 20 and 21, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months or with fine which may extend to twenty lakh`
  line `rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (50113)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Punishment for false or misleading advertisement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50113&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `Any manufacturer or service provider`
  line `who causes a false or misleading advertisement to be made which is prejudicial to the interest of`
  line `consumers shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years and with fine`
  line `which may extend to ten lakh rupees; and for every subsequent offence, be punished with imprisonment`
  line `for a term which may extend to five years and with fine which may extend to fifty lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (50138)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Punishment for manufacturing for sale or storing, selling or distributing or importing products containing adulterant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50138&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever, by himself or by any other person on his behalf,`
  line `manufactures for sale or stores or sells or distributes or imports any product containing an adulterant shall`
  line `be punished, if such act--`
  line
  line `(a) does not result in any injury to the consumer, with imprisonment for a term which may extend`
  line `to six months and with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees;`
  line
  line `(b) causing injury not amounting to grievous hurt to the consumer, with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to one year and with fine which may extend to three lakh rupees;`
  line
  line `(c) causing injury resulting in grievous hurt to the consumer, with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to seven years and with fine which may extend to five lakh rupees; and`
  line
  line `(d) results in the death of a consumer, with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than`
  line `seven years, but which may extend to imprisonment for life and with fine which shall not be less than`
  line `ten lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) The offences under clauses (c) and (d) of sub-section (1) shall be cognizable and non-bailable.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding the punishment under sub-section (1), the court may, in case of first conviction,`
  line `suspend any licence issued to the person referred to in that sub-section, under any law for the time being`
  line `in force, for a period up to two years, and in case of second or subsequent conviction, cancel the licence.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "adulterant" means any material including extraneous matter which is employed or used for`
  line `making a product unsafe;`
  line
  line `(b) "grievous hurt" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in section 320 of the Indian`
  line `Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (50140)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Punishment for manufacturing for sale or for storing or selling or distributing or importing spurious goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50140&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever, by himself or by any other person on his behalf, manufactures for sale or`
  line `stores or sells or distributes or imports any spurious goods shall be punished, if such act--`
  line
  line `(a) causing injury not amounting to grievous hurt to the consumer, with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to one year and with fine which may extend to three lakh rupees;`
  line
  line `(b) causing injury resulting in grievous hurt to the consumer, with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to seven years and with fine which may extend to five lakh rupees;`
  line
  line `(c) results in the death of a consumer, with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than`
  line `seven years, but may extend to imprisonment for life and with fine which shall not be less than ten`
  line `lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) The offences under clauses (b) and (c) of sub-section (1) shall be cognizable and non-bailable.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding the punishment under sub-section (1), the court may, in case of first`
  line `conviction, suspend any licence issued to the person referred to in that sub-section, under any law for the time being in force, for a period up to two years, and in case of second or subsequent conviction,`
  line `cancel the licence.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (50116)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Cognizance of offence by court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50116&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `No cognizance shall be taken by a competent court of any`
  line `offence under sections 88 and 89 except on a complaint filed by the Central Authority or any officer`
  line `authorised by it in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (50117)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title `Vexatious search.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50117&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `The Director General or any other officer, exercising powers under section`
  line `22, who knows that there are no reasonable grounds for so doing, and yet--`
  line
  line `(a) searches, or causes to be searched any premises; or`
  line
  line `(b) seizes any record, register or other document or article, shall, for every such offence, be punished`
  line `with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine which may extend to ten`
  line `thousand rupees or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (50118)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Measures to prevent unfair trade practices in e-commerce, direct selling, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50118&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `For the`
  line `purposes of preventing unfair trade practices in e-commerce, direct selling and also to protect the interest`
  line `and rights of consumers, the Central Government may take such measures in the manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (50132)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title `Presidents, members, Chief Commissioner, Commissioner and certain officers to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50132&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `The Presidents and members of the District Commission, the State Commission and the`
  line `National Commission, and officers and other employees thereof, the Chief Commissioner and the`
  line `Commissioner of the Central Authority, the Director General, the Additional Director General, the`
  line `Director, the Joint Director, the Deputy Director and the Assistant Director and all other officers and`
  line `employees of the Central Authority and other persons performing any duty under this Act, while acting or`
  line `purporting to act in pursuance of any of the provisions of this Act, shall be deemed to be public servants`
  line `within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (50120)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `Compounding of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50120&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any offence punishable under sections 88 and 89, may, either`
  line `before or after the institution of the prosecution, be compounded, on payment of such amount as may be`
  line `prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no compounding of such offence shall be made without the leave of the court before`
  line `which a complaint has been filed under section 92:`
  line
  line `Provided further that such sum shall not, in any case, exceed the maximum amount of the fine, which`
  line `may be imposed under this Act for the offence so compounded.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Authority or any officer as may be specially authorised by him in this behalf, may`
  line `compound offences under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall apply to person who commits the same or similar offence, within`
  line `a period of three years from the date on which the first offence, committed by him, was compounded.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, any second or subsequent offence committed after`
  line `the expiry of a period of three years from the date on which the offence was previously compounded,`
  line `shall be deemed to be a first offence.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an offence has been compounded under sub-section (1), no proceeding or further`
  line `proceeding, as the case may be, shall be taken against the offender in respect of the offence so`
  line compounded.
  line
  line `(5) The acceptance of the sum of money for compounding an offence in accordance with sub-section`
  line `(1) by the Central Authority or an officer of the Central Authority empowered in this behalf shall be`
  line `deemed to amount to an acquittal within the meaning of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of`
  line `1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (50121)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 97
  title `Manner of crediting penalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50121&sectionno=97&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `The penalty collected under section 21 and the amount collected`
  line `under section 96 shall be credited to such fund as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (50122)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 98
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50122&sectionno=98&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Presidents and members of the District Commission, the State Commission and the`
  line `National Commission, the Chief Commissioner, the Commissioner, any officer or employee and other`
  line `person performing any duty under this Act, for any act which is in good faith done or intended to be done`
  line `in pursuance of this Act or under any rule or order made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (50123)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 99
  title `Power to give directions by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50123&sectionno=99&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this Act, the Central Authority, shall, in exercise of its powers or the performance of its`
  line `functions under this Act, be bound by such directions on questions of policy, as the Central Government`
  line `may give in writing to it from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Authority shall, as far as practicable, be given an opportunity to express its`
  line `views before any direction is given under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Central Government whether a question is one of policy or not shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (50124)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 100
  title `Act not in derogation of any other.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50124&sectionno=100&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to and`
  line `not in derogation of the provisions of any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (50125)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 101
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50125&sectionno=101&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules for carrying out any of the provisions contained in this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for, --`
  line
  line `(a) the other class or classes of persons including public utility entities under clause (19) of`
  line `section 2;`
  line
  line `(b) the contest, lottery, game of chance or skill which are to be exempted under item (b) of subclause (iii) of clause (47) of section 2;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner of issuing bill or cash memo or receipt for goods sold or services rendered under`
  line `sub-clause (vii) of clause (47) of section 2;`
  line
  line `(d) the number of other official or non-official members of the Central Council under clause (b)`
  line `of sub-section (2) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(e) the time and place of meeting of Central Council and the procedure for the transaction of its`
  line `business under sub-section (2) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(f) the number of Commissioners in the Central Authority under sub-section (2) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(g) the qualifications for appointment, method of recruitment, procedure of appointment, term of`
  line `office, salaries and allowances, resignation, removal and other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Chief Commissioner and other Commissioners of the Central Authority under section 11;`
  line
  line `(h) the salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `officers and other employees of the Central Authority under sub-section (2) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(i) the qualifications for appointment of Director General, Additional Director General, Director,`
  line `Joint Director, Deputy Director and Assistant Director and the manner of appointment under subsection (2) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(j) the manner of taking copies or extracts of document, record or article seized or produced`
  line `before returning to the person under sub-section (3) of section 22;`
  line
  line `(k) the officer and the manner of disposing of articles which are subject to speedy or natural`
  line `decay under sub-section (4) of section 22;`
  line
  line `(l) the form and manner for preparing annual statement of accounts by the Central Authority in`
  line `consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India under sub-section (1) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(m) the form in which, and the time within which, an annual report, other reports and returns may`
  line `be prepared by the Central Authority under sub-section (1) of section 27;`
  line
  line `(n) the qualifications for appointment, method of recruitment, procedure for appointment, term of`
  line `office, resignation and removal of President and members of the District Commission under section`
  line 29;
  line
  line `(o) the other value of goods and services in respect of which the District Commission shall have`
  line `jurisdiction to entertain complaints under proviso to sub-section (1) of section 34;`
  line
  line `(p) the manner of electronically filing complaint under the proviso to sub-section (1) of section`
  line 35;
  line
  line `(q) the fee, electronic form and the manner of payment of fee for filing complaint under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 35;`
  line
  line `(r) the cases which may not be referred for settlement by mediation under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 37;`
  line
  line `(s) the manner of authentication of goods sampled in case of the National Commission under`
  line `clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 38;`
  line
  line `(t) any other matter which may be prescribed under clause (f) of sub-section (9) of section 38;`
  line
  line `(u) the fund where the amount obtained may be credited and the manner of utilisation of such`
  line `amount under sub-section (2) of section 39;`
  line
  line `(v) the form and the manner in which appeal may be preferred to the State Commission under`
  line `section 41;`
  line
  line `(w) the qualifications for appointment, method of recruitment, procedure for appointment, term of`
  line `office, resignation and removal of the President and members of the State Commission under section`
  line 43;
  line
  line `(x) the other value of goods and services in respect of which the State Commission shall have`
  line `jurisdiction under the proviso to sub-clause (i) of clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 47;`
  line
  line `(y) the form and manner of filing appeal to the National Commission, and the manner of`
  line `depositing fifty per cent. of the amount before filing appeal, under sub-section (1) of section 51;`
  line
  line `(z) the number of members of the National Commission under clause (b) of section 54;`
  line
  line `(za) the qualifications, appointment, term of office, salaries and allowances, resignation, removal`
  line `and other terms and conditions of service of the President and members of the National Commission`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 55;`
  line
  line `(zb) the salaries and allowances payable to, and other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `officers and other employees of the National Commission under sub-section (3) of section 57;`
  line
  line `(zc) the other value of goods and services in respect of which the National Commission shall have`
  line `jurisdiction under the proviso to sub-clause (i) of clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 58;`
  line
  line `(zd) the manner of depositing fifty per cent. of the amount under the second proviso to section 67;`
  line
  line `(ze) the form in which the National Commission and the State Commission shall furnish`
  line `information to the Central Government under sub-section (4) of section 70;`
  line
  line `(zf) the persons in the consumer mediation cell under sub-section (3) of section 74;`
  line
  line `(zg) the measures to be taken by the Central Government to prevent unfair trade practices in`
  line `e-commerce, direct selling under section 94;`
  line
  line `(zh) the amount for compounding offences under sub-section (1) of section 96;`
  line
  line `(zi) the fund to which the penalty and amount collected shall be credited under section 97; and`
  line
  line `(zj) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed, or in respect of which provisions are to`
  line `be, or may be, made by rules`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (50126)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 102
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50126&sectionno=102&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Governments may, by`
  line `notification, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, frame model rules in respect of all or any of the`
  line `matters with respect to which the State Government may make rules under this section, and where`
  line `any such model rules have been framed in respect of any such matter, they shall apply to the State`
  line `until the rules in respect of that matter is made by the State Government and while making any such`
  line `rules, so far as is practicable, they shall conform to such model rules.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the other class or classes of persons including public utility entities under clause (19) of`
  line `section 2;`
  line
  line `(b) the contest, lottery, game of chance or skill which are to be exempted under item (b) of`
  line `sub-clause (iii) of clause (47) of section 2;`
  line
  line `(c) the number of other official or non-official members of the State Council under`
  line `clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(d) the time and place of meeting of the State Council and the procedure for the transaction`
  line `of its business under sub-section (4) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(e) the number of other official and non-official members of District Council under clause`
  line `(b) of sub-section (2) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(f) the time and place of meeting of the District Council and procedure for the transaction of`
  line `its business under sub-section (4) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(g) the number of members of the District Commission under clause (b) of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 28;`
  line
  line `(h) the salaries and allowances payable to, and other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `President and members of the District Commission under section 30;`
  line
  line `(i) the salaries and allowances payable to, and other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `officers and other employees of the District Commission under sub-section (3) of section 33;`
  line
  line `(j) the manner of authentication of goods sampled by the State Commission and the District`
  line `Commission under clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 38;`
  line
  line `(k) the manner of depositing fifty per cent. of the amount before filing appeal under second`
  line `proviso to section 41;`
  line
  line `(l) the number of members of the State Commission under sub-section (3) of section 42;`
  line
  line `(m) the salaries and allowances payable to, and other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `President and members of the State Commission under section 44;`
  line
  line `(n) the salaries and allowances payable to, and other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `officers and other employees of the State Commission under sub-section (3) of section 46;`
  line
  line `(o) the form in which the State Commission shall furnish information to the State`
  line `Government under sub-section (5) of section 70;`
  line
  line `(p) the persons in the consumer mediation cell under sub-section (3) of section 74;`
  line
  line `(q) any other matter which is to be, or may be prescribed, or in respect of which provisions`
  line `are to be, or may be, made by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (50127)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 103
  title `Power of National Commission to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50127&sectionno=103&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Commission may,`
  line `with the previous approval of the Central Government, by notification, make regulations not inconsistent with this Act to provide for all matters for which provision is necessary or expedient for the purpose of`
  line `giving effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `make provisions for--`
  line
  line `(a) the costs for adjournment to be imposed by the District Commission under the second`
  line `proviso to sub-section (7) of section 38;`
  line
  line `(b) the costs for adjournment to be imposed by the State Commission or the National`
  line `Commission, as the case may be, under the second proviso to section 52;`
  line
  line `(c) the maintenance of any other information by the consumer mediation cell under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 74;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner of submission of quarterly report by consumer mediation cell to the District`
  line `Commission, the State Commission or the National Commission under sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 74;`
  line
  line `(e) the qualifications and experience required for empanelment as mediator, the procedure for`
  line `empanelment, the manner of training empanelled mediators, the fee payable to empanelled`
  line `mediator, the terms and conditions for empanelment, the code of conduct for empanelled mediators,`
  line `the grounds on which, and the manner in which, empanelled mediators shall be removed or`
  line `empanelment shall be cancelled and the other matters relating thereto under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 75;`
  line
  line `(f) the conditions for re-empanelment of mediators for another term under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 75;`
  line
  line `(g) the other facts to be disclosed by mediators under clause (c) of section 77;`
  line
  line `(h) the time within which, and the manner in which, mediation may be conducted under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 79; and`
  line
  line `(i) such other matter for which provision is to be, or may be, made by regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (50128)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 104
  title `Power of Central Authority to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50128&sectionno=104&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Authority may, with the`
  line `previous approval of the Central Government, by notification, make regulations not inconsistent with this`
  line `Act, for the purpose of giving effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the procedure for engaging experts and professionals and the number of such experts and`
  line `professionals under sub-section (3) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure for transaction of business and the allocation of business of the Chief`
  line `Commissioner and Commissioner under sub-section (1) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(c) the form, manner and time within which, inquiries or investigation made by the`
  line `Director-General shall be submitted to the Central Authority under sub-section (5) of section 15;`
  line and
  line
  line `(d) such other matter for which provision is to be, or may be, made by regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (50129)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 105
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before each House of Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50129&sectionno=105&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every rule and every`
  line `regulation made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of`
  line `Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session`
  line `or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the`
  line `session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or`
  line `regulation or both Houses agree that the rule or regulation shall thereafter have effect only in such`
  line `modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule or`
  line regulation.
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made by a State Government under this Act shall be laid as soon as may be after it is`
  line `made, before the State Legislature.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (50130)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 106
  title `Power to Remove Difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50130&sectionno=106&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order in the Official Gazette, make such provisions not inconsistent`
  line `with the provisions of this Act as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (50131)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 107
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903&sectionId=50131&sectionno=107&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201935_1596441164903
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Consumer Protection Act, 1986 (68 of 1986) is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken or purported to have been done or`
  line `taken under the Act hereby repealed shall, in so far as it is not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act,`
  line `be deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The mention of particular matters in sub-section (2) shall not be held to prejudice or affect the`
  line `general application of section 6 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897) with regard to the effect of`
  line repeal.
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
